### =========================================
### 1. STUDENT SERVICE TESTS
### =========================================

### 1A. Create a Student
POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rahul Sharma",
  "email": "rahul.sharma@example.com"
}

### 1B. Create a Second Student
POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Priya Patel",
  "email": "priya.patel@example.com"
}

### 1C. Get All Students
GET http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/students

### 1D. Get a Specific Student (ID: 1)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/students/1

### 1E. Update a Student (ID: 1)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/students/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rahul S.",
  "email": "rahul.sharma@university.edu"
}

### =========================================
### 2. COURSE SERVICE TESTS
### =========================================

### 2A. Create a Course
POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_name": "Cloud Computing 101"
}

### 2B. Create a Second Course
POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_name": "Advanced Docker Containerization"
}

### 2C. Get All Courses
GET http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/courses

### 2D. Get a Specific Course (ID: 1)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/courses/1

### 2E. Update a Course (ID: 1)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/courses/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_name": "Cloud Computing & Microservices"
}

### =========================================
### 3. ENROLLMENT SERVICE TESTS 
### (Integration & Fault Testing)
### =========================================

### 3A. Create a Valid Enrollment (Student 1 into Course 1)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student_id": 1,
  "course_id": 1
}

### 3B. Test Data Validation (Fail: Student 99 doesn't exist)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student_id": 99,
  "course_id": 1
}

### 3C. Get All Enrollments
GET http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/enrollments

### 3D. Get a Specific Enrollment (ID: 1)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1

### 3E. Update an Enrollment (Change Student 1 to Course 2)
### (This now works because Course 2 has not been deleted yet!)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student_id": 1,
  "course_id": 2
}

### =========================================
### 4. DELETION / CLEANUP TESTS
### =========================================

### 4A. Delete an Enrollment (ID: 1)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1

### 4B. Delete a Course (ID: 2)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/courses/2

### 4C. Delete a Student (ID: 2)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1/students/2